This paper proposes a method for obtaining sentence-level embeddings using a sequential encoder-decoder model and a pair-wise discriminator. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as paraphrase generation and sentiment analysis, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of a sequential encoder-decoder model and a discriminator also suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly found in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings for image captioning, which could suggest a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) or neural networks (cs.NE).
